Apr 20 2007 	Absolutly 5 star	We stayed at The Fairmont for 5 nights over Easter. Never been to Dubai and was curious to see what all the fuss was about! I researched the hotel thru Trip advisor and we were very pleased with what we got!Beautiful hotel, immaculatley kept in every aspect.The rooms are large, we were on the 27th floor with a sea &amp; city view.Marble bathroms with Miller Harris products,robes and slippers all that you would expect from a 5 star hotel. All the staff were fantastic, smiling all the time and nothing was too much trouble for them. For example I sneezed at the pool one day, next minute September the poll boy brought me a box of tissues, thats what I call service. Only at Reids Palace in Maderia have I had that level of service!!We stayed by the pool every day,I am a total sun worshipper and had choosen this hotel as no one had complained about the sun leaving the pool at 3 or 4pm. I was a little stressed the first day when we arrived to see a very small pool and no sun loungers available! I was then told to go to the Sunset pool (we were at the Sunrise) and the sun would be around at 1pm! This was the only day we had a lounger issue!The first night we had dinner in the hotel, I had done some research and one helpful &quot;Tripper&quot; had posted the complete &quot;Dubia Time Out&quot; best restuarant . As the best Global was at &quot;The Fairmont&quot; we decided to try.A little disapointing,possible too much choice, rather over welming.We ordered a &quot;Fruits de Mer&quot; which tasted of fishy cotton wool,not really the hotels fault, sometimes these over grown prawns etc look fantastic but the taste is certainly no senstion!! The second night we went to the best Latin American restaurant at The Jumeriah beach, cant remember its name as it was not a very memorable meal! It was at that point we decided to give up on 5 star hotel restaurants!The Souk Medinat had a great Lebanese Restaurant which I would recommend,it was memorable but sorry cant remeber the name! You can have Shisha pipes ( hubbly bubbly) there which is rather fun.Off course we went to The Mall of the Emeriates, just to see what all the fuss was about.Very impressive,but I was not in the shopping mood (lucky husband)We also visited the Emirates Tower for cocktails, very good, excellent view. we were too late for bar at The Grosvenor House and The Buddah bar was closed for a private party! We coulnt get a reservation at &quot;Al Burg Arab&quot; yes I know i said I was done with 5 stars but this was 7 stars so it does not count! The Gold Souk was a waste of time, tacky, tatty shops selling rubbish unless you like cheap gold that is! In a nut shell, Dubai is very interesting,great hotels, good shops, fantastic weather . The shopping is good but no better than London or New York, I guess if you dont live in either of these cities then it is great. Its not a bargin place to shop, tax free or not!. I would certainly visit again. Next time I would stay nearer the beach , now I know my way around the place. I would certainly stay at The Fairmont is I was passing thru for a day or two, as it is close to the airport.	
