Apr 5 2007 	Not the best in Dubai	Stayed with my wife in the Fairmont for 2 nights from 3/4/07 to 5/4/07 after spending 3 nights in Grand Hyatt Dubai. Fairmont Hotel is a typical 5 star hotel but with no extras. Following our stay at Grand Hyatt, we felt that we have been downgraded by moving to the Fairmont although they charge same rate per night as Grand Hyatt. The swimming pools are much smaller and the rooms are half size of those in Grand Hyatt.The shower facilities are very averge and the lobby is standard with no special features.Having said that, the service was very good with very nice staff smiling all the time. The location is very handy being on Sheik Zayed street close to the major malls in Dubai. Fairmont looks nice from outside with very beautiful lighting at night. If you are lucky as we were and get a room on a high floor you can see most of Dubai towers including Burj Al arab from your room window.I and my wife agreed that we would give the Fairmont Dubai 7 out of 10 and we would try another hotel besides Grand Hyatt on our next visit to Dubai.	
Apr 2 2007	Good business hotel but...	I stayed for three nights although it was supposed to be 4. When I arrived I was told that they did not have a room for me that night and that they would put me up in the Shangri La for the first night at their expense. This was happening a lot that evening as several others around reception were arguing about missing reservations. As I was there on business this was a pain because it took time out of the following day to move back and the room at the Shangri La was not great.Compensation was in the form of not paying for my first night and free business lounge access at the Fairmont. Not bad but I expected more.Other than that this is a fine hotel, the food is very good, especially the Spectrum restaurant (7 different types of food in one place) and the cigar bar is well worth a visit. Overall it's a bit chic and trendy but its well located and you can walk to the convention centre in less than 10 minutes.	
Feb 27 2007 	One of the Best Fairmonts in the World	Dubai is full of five-star hotels - they're everywhere. More and more are being built to cater to the burgeoning tourist industry - lots of resort-like developments up already and planned.If you're a future tourist to Dubai, I think there are an array of properties one might find are more suitable than the Fairmont. But, if you're in town on business, the Fairmont Dubai would be an excellent choice.It's a large property, on Dubai's main thoroughfare - you'd think this is, logistically, a plus, but the traffic has become far worse in the two years since my last visit. There's not much around the Fairmont, most of the city continues to be pedestrian-unfriendly. The newer hotel properties tend to be built further away (more north away from the airport) from the old-city, Dubai Creek area - the Fairmont is, seemingly, right in the middle of everything.Spacious rooms, with lots of amenities. Very clean and polished. The room had everything I needed including a daily fruit basket and a lot of bottled water. A couple of small problems: my key card did not always work very well, I had a couple of problems with my tv (it was running off a computer in the room - I later found out I could just reboot it myself) and the shower leaked a bit (nice and powerful though).If you're in town for a trade show at the convention centre, the Fairmont is strategically located near Sheik Al Zayed's only overpass, so it's a short walk to the convention. The Novotel and Hotel Ibis are closer, but are not of the same high standard as the Fairmont - and neither is the Al Murooj (my colleagues stayed in these hotels and had provided comment after seeing the Fairmont).Food note: there's a Lebanese restaurant beside a KFC which is about a five minute walk south of the Fairmont. Nothing fancy, but great food and a good price.	
Jan 28 2007 	Good value for a stopover	My wife and I stayed here on the first night of our honeymoon - a single night stopover in Dubai. Stayed in a Gold Deluxe Room.Our personal rating system for this trip: Overall - 7/10 (me), 7/10 (wife)Value - 7/10 (me), 6/10 (wife) ... but better than other Dubai options!!Firstly, the destination. We didn't rate Dubai highly, so if you can get transfers to your next destination without big delays, do so (in our opinion!). Then again, we didn't spend time in the Jumeirah Beach area, so that may be why. Shopping - no better than home (Melbourne, Australia) ... though that excludes the gold markets, which we were leaving until Istanbul later in our trip. A cruise on Dubai Creek was mildly interesting (if not a welcome relief from the heat!), but not great value for money - we definitely wouldn't recommend a dinner cruise and are glad we opted for the daytime version. Still, it's one of those places that's good to see once ... just plenty of others that will remain higher on our list!HOTELPositives - VERY comfortable beds &amp; pillows, good sized bathroom, reasonably quiet, helpful &amp; professional staff, close to airport, around 20 mins in a taxi to most attractions (AED 20-30 each way), return transfers included in the room rate, Gold lounge access was fantastic value and something i'd highly recommend for those staying here.Negatives - room was smaller than expected but OK, more tailored to business clientele than tourists - a positive or negative depending on what you're looking for!	
